# HTMLPreview - HTML Snippet Hosting Service

## Overview

HTMLPreview is a Vercel-deployed Next.js application that provides an authenticated API for storing HTML snippets and serving them on public URLs. Think of it as a pastebin/Gist service specifically for HTML content.

## Deployment

- **Platform**: Vercel
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.0 (App Router)
- **Storage**: Vercel Blob (object storage)

## Core Functionality

### Write Operations
- `POST /api/snippets` - Create snippets (requires `API_WRITE_TOKEN` or user-generated token)
- Accepts: `title` (optional), `html` (required), `passphrase` (optional), `id` (optional, for updates)
- Returns: `{ id, apiUrl, publicUrl }`
- `DELETE /api/snippets/:id` - Delete snippets (requires authentication)

### Read Operations
- `GET /api/snippets/:id` - Fetch snippet JSON (public, but requires passphrase if protected)
- `GET /p/:id` - View snippet in browser (server-rendered page with iframe)

### Admin Dashboard
- `GET /admin` - Admin dashboard (protected, requires Google OAuth)
- `GET /api/admin/tokens` - List user's API tokens
- `POST /api/admin/tokens` - Generate new API token
- `DELETE /api/admin/tokens` - Delete API token

### Security
- Write auth: Bearer token (supports both `API_WRITE_TOKEN` env var and user-generated tokens)
- Admin auth: Google OAuth via NextAuth.js v5
- Per-snippet protection: Optional passphrase hashed with PBKDF2
- HTML rendering: Sandboxed iframes for isolation

## Key Files

- `src/lib/auth.ts` - Bearer token authentication (supports global and user tokens)
- `src/lib/passphrase.ts` - PBKDF2 passphrase hashing/verification
- `src/lib/store.ts` - Vercel Blob storage operations (snippets and user tokens)
- `src/lib/types.ts` - TypeScript types for snippets and user tokens
- `src/lib/auth-config.ts` - NextAuth.js configuration with Google OAuth
- `src/auth.ts` - NextAuth.js handlers and auth functions
- `src/middleware.ts` - Route protection for admin pages
- `src/app/api/snippets/route.ts` - POST endpoint for creating snippets
- `src/app/api/snippets/[id]/route.ts` - GET/DELETE endpoints for snippets
- `src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` - NextAuth.js API route handler
- `src/app/api/admin/tokens/route.ts` - Token management API endpoints
- `src/app/admin/page.tsx` - Admin dashboard page (server component)
- `src/app/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx` - Admin dashboard UI (client component)
- `src/app/p/[id]/page.tsx` - Public view page with passphrase form

## Environment Variables

Required for deployment:
- `API_WRITE_TOKEN` - Optional secret token for write authentication (backward compatible)
- `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN` - Automatically set by Vercel when you create a Blob store (no manual setup needed)
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` - Required for admin dashboard (Google OAuth)
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` - Required for admin dashboard (Google OAuth)
- `AUTH_SECRET` - Required for NextAuth.js (generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`)

**Google OAuth Setup:**
- Redirect URI must be: `https://htmlpreview-phi.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/google`
- Configure in Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials

## Storage Schema

Snippets stored in Vercel Blob with pathname pattern: `snippets/<uuid>.json`

Data structure:
```typescript
{
  id: string;
  html: string;
  title?: string;
  passphraseHash?: string; // PBKDF2 hash (salt:hash format)
  createdAt: string;
  createdBy: string;
}
```

User tokens stored in Vercel Blob with pathname pattern: `tokens/<userId>/<tokenId>.json`

Token structure:
```typescript
{
  userId: string;
  token: string; // Secure random token (64 hex characters)
  createdAt: string;
  name?: string; // Optional token name
}
```

## When Making Changes

- Always check Vercel deployment requirements
- Ensure environment variables are set in Vercel dashboard (including Google OAuth credentials)
- Create a Blob store in Vercel dashboard (BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN is auto-injected)
- Remember: passphrases are one-way hashed - cannot be recovered
- HTML is rendered in sandboxed iframes - scripts are isolated
- Admin routes are protected by middleware - unauthenticated users redirect to `/api/auth/signin`
- API authentication checks both global `API_WRITE_TOKEN` and user-generated tokens (timing-safe comparison)
- User tokens are stored per-user in Vercel Blob for isolation
